  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum number of set bits in the product of 2023 and n. Since n can be any integer, this is equivalent to finding the minimum Hamming weight of any multiple of 2023. This is a number theory problem related to the order of 2 in the ring Z/2023Z or finding a power of 2 that is congruent to 1 modulo a divisor of 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "number_theory_expert",
      "instructions": "Find the prime factorization of 2023. Determine if there exists an n such that 2023*n is a power of 2 (which would make k(n)=1), or if the minimum k(n) must be greater than 1. Specifically, check if 2023 is a power of 2 or if any power of 2 is a multiple of 2023. If not, investigate the smallest possible number of bits by looking for the smallest m such that there exists a sum of m powers of 2 that is divisible by 2023."
    },
    {
      "label": "combinatorial_search_expert",
      "instructions": "Test small values of k for the existence of n. For k=1, check if 2023 divides 2^a. For k=2, check if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b (which is equivalent to checking if 2^(a-b) is congruent to -1 modulo 2023 or if 2^c is congruent to 1 modulo 2023/gcd(2023, 2^b)). Systematically check if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + ... for increasing numbers of terms until a solution is found."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent will take the prime factorization from the first helper to determine the constraints on n. It will then use the search results from the second helper to identify the smallest k for which a sum of k powers of 2 is divisible by 2023. The final answer will be the smallest k found."
}

